<TEI xmlns="http://www.tei-c.org/ns/1.0" xmlns:frus="http://history.state.gov/frus/ns/1.0"><text><body><div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1919-07-26T12:00:00-05:00" frus:doc-dateTime-min="1919-07-26T12:00:00-05:00" n="243" subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d243">
                            <note rend="inline" type="source">Paris Peace Conf. 184.011102/203:
                                Telegram</note>
                            <head><hi rend="italic">The <gloss type="from">Commission to Negotiate
                                        Peace</gloss> to Mr. <persName type="to">Albert
                                        Halstead</persName></hi></head>
                            <opener><dateline rendition="#right"><placeName><hi rend="smallcaps">Paris</hi></placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1919-07-26T18:00:00+01:00">July 26, 1919—6
                                    p.m.</date></dateline></opener>
                            <p>141. Your telegrams 646, 647, 654.<note n="83" xml:id="d243fn83"><hi rend="italic">Ante</hi>, <ref target="#pg_613">pp. 613</ref>
                                    and <ref target="#pg_614">614</ref>.</note> Commission does not
                                wish you to carry on any negotiations with Boehm. You should have
                                nothing whatsoever to do with the matter directly or indirectly.</p>
                            <closer><hi rend="smallcaps">Am</hi>[<hi rend="smallcaps">erican</hi>]
                                    <hi rend="smallcaps">Mission</hi></closer>
                        </div>
                        </body></text></TEI>